  "body": "# ðŸš€ Feature Request\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nIf geth is running behind nginx proxy to serve tls encription with self signed certificate, the connection to the geth client fails because the beacon node can't verify the certification issuer:\r\n`[2020-11-15 02:17:04] ERROR powchain: Could not connect to powchain endpoint error=Post \"https://<ipgeth>/\": x509: certificate signed by unknown authority`\r\n\r\n### Describe the solution you'd like\r\n\r\nPlease add some kind of `--no-check-certificate` parameter to prysm beacon-node to skip tls verification\r\n\r\n### Describe alternatives you've considered\r\n\r\nWorkaround would be to use real CA or let's encrypto certificates\r\n",
